revision.text:
In April and May 2016, India experienced a major [[heat wave]]. A national record high temperature of 51.0&nbsp;°C (123.8&nbsp;°F) was set in the town of [[Phalodi]], in the state of [[Rajasthan]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Agarwal|first1=Vibhuti|title=Indian Heat Wave Breaks Record for Highest Temperature|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/indiarealtime/2016/05/20/indian-heat-wave-breaks-record-for-highest-temperature/|website=Wall Street Journal|publisher=Wall Street Journal|accessdate=22 May 2016|ref=record high}}</ref><ref name="cnn-record">{{cite web|last1=Wu|first1=Huizhong|title=Mercury rising: India records its highest temperature ever|url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/05/20/asia/india-record-temperature/|website=CNN|accessdate=22 May 2016}}</ref> A total of over 1600 people have died and 330 million affected. There are also water shortages. Drought has worsened the heat wave.<ref>{{cite web|title=Western Indian State Tries to Cope With Record Heat Wave|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/western-indian-state-tries-to-cope-with-record-heat-wave-1463846290|website=Wall Street Journal|publisher=Wall Street Journal|accessdate=22 May 2016|ref=west India}}</ref>

