{{Expand German|Freiheits- und Einheitsdenkmal|date=April 2011}}
[[File:Das_Nationale_Freiheits_und_Einheitsdenkmal.jpg|thumb|The monument viewed from the Schinkelplatz]]
The '''Monument to Freedom and Unity''' (''{{lang-de|Denkmal für Freiheit und Einheit}}'') is a planned national German monument in [[Berlin]] commemorating the country's peaceful [[German reunification|reunification]] in 1990 and earlier 18th, 19th and 20th century unification movements.

It was agreed on 9 November 2007 by a decree of the [[Bundestag]].<ref>[http://dip21.bundestag.de/dip21/btd/16/069/1606974.pdf Deutscher Bundestag, Drucksache 16/6974]</ref> The decree proposed the site of the former [[National Kaiser Wilhelm Monument]] on the ''Schlossfreiheit'' for the new structure, next to the site of the [[City Palace, Berlin|City Palace Berlin]] that is reconstructed since 2013. The monument would carry on its surface the slogans of the 1989 demonstrations: "''Wir sind das Volk, Wir sind ein Volk''" which means (We are the People, We are one People).<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2011/apr/18/berlin-monument-wall-fall|title=Berlin selects giant rocking dish as monument to unification|author=Abby d'Arcy Hughes|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=19 April 2011|accessdate=19 April 2011}}</ref>

In early June 2017, the Bundestag decided to start construction of the memorial in front of the City Palace according to the design of Milla & Partner. It is to be inaugurated on the 30th anniversary of the [[fall of the Berlin Wall]] on 9 November 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tagesspiegel.de/kultur/einheitsdenkmal-in-berlin-bundestag-segnet-die-wippe-ab/19883712.html|title=Bundestag segnet die Wippe ab|author=Christiane Peitz|work=[[Der Tagesspiegel]]|language=German|date=2 June 2016|accessdate=23 August 2017}}
</ref>

